The Australian descendants of eight ANZAC veterans have showed off their relatives ' wartime medals and photographs in a moving commemorative photo series .
Photographer Mark Kolbe travelled around Australia to meet the grandchildren , great-grandchildren , sons and daughters of just some of the Australian armed forces who landed in Gallipoli nearly 100 years ago .
Among the soldiers are letters sent by soldiers informing their loved ones of their discharge from the Australian Imperial Force .
